PRETTY RACHEL pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, dueled from the four path around the bend and chased the winner home in the lane, managing to get the head bob for second place. DAILY BRIEFING trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the three path around the turn, and continued to gain ground late, just missing second place. IDEAL BREEZE led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the turn, was caught in midstretch and kept on the finish, narrowly missing second. SASSY LIKE JULIA tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and weakened in the final furlong.

BARAK tracked the leaders on the outside through the opening quarter, launched a bid from the two path coming around the bend, dueled down the lane and gave way late, the best of the rest. HELLO SUCKER chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, couldn't go with the top two in the stretch and chased those two home. ALTAIR hopped up leaving the gate, raced off the pace on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and improved position mildly in the lane, no match for the top two. PURE OF HEART bumped lightly with the horses to both sides leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack through the opening stages, came around the bend in the four path and never threatened. FOREVER SAUCY raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and made no bid. DISCREET DEVIL led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn and tired in the stretch. MASTER SERGEANT raced at the back of the pack on the outside in the early going, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground around the turn and was not a factor.
